  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Comprehensive legal definitions of money laundering\n- Criminal penalties for offenses\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Banking regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Risk assessment protocols\n- Internal control systems\n- Regular audits and reporting\n\n6. Legal Consequences\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n7. Jurisdictional Variations\n- Different countries have unique implementation approaches\n- Varying severity of penalties\n- Specific regulatory requirements\n\n8. Financial Sector Obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Enhanced due diligence for high-risk clients\n\nThis framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
